Boiling, With Loss Of Acid Constituents And Resulting Rise In Ph Caused Precipitation Of Ores And Formation Of Intensely Altered Sericitic Cap Above Ore.  Cap Is Actually Coalescence Of Alteration Fans Spreading Upward And Outward Through More Fractured And Porous Rock In Major Fault Zones And Along Parallel And Antithetic Fractures In Hanging Wall.
